cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this dataset, please cite the accompanying paper."
title: "Multi-Source Memory Benchmark (Selective QA Diagnostic Testbed)"
abstract: >
  A diagnostic testbed for selective question-answering (ANSWER /
  abstain) over conflicting multi-source personal memory. Each
  persona has five evidence streams projected from a single latent
  event table with known, controlled per-source distortions, allowing
  methods to be measured against a deterministic latent ground truth
  rather than against any single source. 4 seeds x 480 personas x 18
  questions = 34,560 instances spanning 8 reasoning types. The
  accompanying paper compares baselines, structured fusion methods,
  and frontier LLMs.
type: dataset
